'''田植踊'''（たうえおどり） *[[宮城県]][[仙台市]][[太白区]]秋保町に伝わる[[国際連合教育科学文化機関|ユネスコ]][[無形文化遺産]]の民俗芸能。[[秋保の田植踊]]を参照。 *宮城県[[黒川郡]][[富谷町]]富谷に伝わる[[宮城県指定文化財一覧#無形|宮城県の無形民俗文化財]]の民俗芸能。[[富谷田植踊り]]を参照。 *[[岩手県]][[紫波郡]][[紫波町]]山屋に伝わる[[重要無形民俗文化財]]の民俗芸能。[[山屋の田植踊]]を参照。 *岩手県[[岩手郡]][[滝沢村]]大沢に伝わる滝沢村の[[無形民俗文化財]]の民俗芸能。[[大沢田植踊り]]を参照。 *[[山形県]][[東根市]]小田島に伝わる東根市の無形民俗文化財の民俗芸能。[[小田島田植踊り]]を参照。 *[[福島県]][[二本松市]]石東町・錦町・北トロミに伝わる重要無形民俗文化財の民俗芸能。[[石井の七福神と田植踊]]を参照。 *福島県[[双葉郡]][[浪江町]]津島に伝わる福島県の無形文化財の民俗芸能。[[津島の田植踊]]を参照。 *福島県[[本宮市]]稲沢字梅ケ久保に伝わる本宮市の無形民俗文化財の民俗芸能。[[稲沢御田植踊り]]を参照。 *[[青森県]][[八戸市|八戸]]地方に伝わる重要無形民俗文化財の民俗芸能。[[八戸のえんぶり]]を参照。
{{aimai}}
{{日本の伝統芸能}}
{{デフォルトソート:たうえおとり}} [[Category:日本の伝統芸能]]

'''Taue Odori''' (田植踊) is a form of {{ill|yoshuku performing arts|ja|予祝芸能|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Ta-asobi|lt=tanuki-themed ceremonies|ja|田遊び|12=draft|12=draft}}, primarily performed in the {{ill|Tohoku region|ja|東北地方|12=draft|12=draft}} of Japan, particularly in {{ill|Miyagi Prefecture|ja|宮城県|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Iwate Prefecture|ja|岩手県|12=draft|12=draft}}, during the {{ill|Small New Year|ja|小正月|12=draft|12=draft}} season. It is believed to have evolved into a {{ill|furyu dance|ja|風流踊|1=Furyu-odori|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Overview ==
Unlike {{ill|Ta-asobi|lt=tanuki-themed ceremonies|ja|田遊び|12=draft|12=draft}}, which often simulate {{ill|rice cultivation|ja|稲作|12=draft|12=draft}} through symbolic gestures, Taue Odori is characterized by its strong {{ill|performance art|ja|芸能|12=draft|12=draft}} aspects. It is typically performed by {{ill|village|ja|村|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|youth|ja|青年|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|boys|ja|少年|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|girls|ja|少女|12=draft|12=draft}}, accompanied by a leader called "Yajuro" and wearing {{ill|decorative flower hats|ja|花笠|12=draft|12=draft}}. Performers visit {{ill|households|ja|住宅|12=draft|12=draft}}, performing songs and dances, often following a recitation by Yajuro.
In some cases, the performance begins with a {{ill|dedication|ja|奉納|12=draft|12=draft}} at {{ill|shrines|ja|神社|12=draft|12=draft}} or {{ill|temples|ja|寺院|12=draft|12=draft}} before visiting homes. Variations exist, such as the inclusion of {{ill|Ta-no-Kami|ja|田の神|Ta-no-Kami=Ta-no-Kami|lt=rice-field gods|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Seven Lucky Gods|ja|七福神|12=draft|12=draft}}, celebrating the {{ill|New Year|ja|新年|12=draft|12=draft}} in unique ways.
== Representative Taue Odori Performances ==
* {{ill|Akiu no Taue Odori|ja|秋保の田植踊|12=draft|12=draft}}: A {{ill|UNESCO Intangible Cultural Heritage|ja|ユネスコ無形文化遺産|12=draft|12=draft}} folk performing art from {{ill|Akihisa|ja|秋保町|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Sendai City|ja|仙台市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Taihaku Ward|ja|太白区|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Miyagi Prefecture|ja|宮城県|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Aiko Taue Odori|ja|愛子の田植踊|12=draft|12=draft}}: A folk performing art designated as a {{ill|Miyagi Prefecture Cultural Heritage|ja|宮城県指定文化財一覧#無形|12=draft|12=draft}}, from {{ill|Aiko|ja|愛子|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Aoba Ward|ja|青葉区|12=draft|12=draft}}, Sendai City. * {{ill|Tomiyama Taue Odori|ja|富谷田植踊り|12=draft|12=draft}}: A folk performing art from {{ill|Tomiyama|ja|富谷市|12=draft|12=draft}}, designated as an intangible cultural heritage of {{ill|Miyagi Prefecture|ja|宮城県|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Yamaya Taue Odori|ja|山屋の田植踊|12=draft|12=draft}}: A {{ill|National Important Intangible Folk Cultural Asset|ja|重要無形民俗文化財|12=draft|12=draft}} from {{ill|Yamaya|ja|紫波町|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Shiwa District|ja|紫波郡|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Iwate Prefecture|ja|岩手県|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Osawa Taue Odori|ja|大沢田植踊り|12=draft|12=draft}}: A folk performing art designated as an intangible cultural heritage of {{ill|Takasaki City|ja|滝沢市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Iwate Prefecture|ja|岩手県|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Kodashima Taue Odori|ja|小田島田植踊り|12=draft|12=draft}}: A folk performing art from {{ill|Kodashima|ja|小田島|12=draft|12=draft}}, designated as an intangible cultural heritage of {{ill|Higashine City|ja|東根市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Yamagata Prefecture|ja|山形県|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Ishii no Shichifukujin to Taue Odori|ja|石井の七福神と田植踊|12=draft|12=draft}}: A {{ill|National Important Intangible Folk Cultural Asset|ja|重要無形民俗文化財|12=draft|12=draft}} from {{ill|Ishi District|ja|石東町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nishiki District|ja|錦町|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Kita Toromi|ja|北トロミ|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Nihonmatsu City|ja|二本松市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Tsubame Taue Odori|ja|津島の田植踊|12=draft|12=draft}}: A folk performing art designated as an intangible cultural heritage of {{ill|Namie Town|ja|浪江町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Futaba District|ja|双葉郡|12=draft|12=draft}}, Fukushima Prefecture. * {{ill|Inazawa Otaue Odori|ja|稲沢御田植踊り|12=draft|12=draft}}: A folk performing art designated as an intangible cultural heritage of {{ill|Inazawa|ja|稲沢字梅ケ久保|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Motomiya City|ja|本宮市|12=draft|12=draft}}, Fukushima Prefecture. * {{ill|Hachinohe Emburi|ja|八戸のえんぶり|12=draft|12=draft}}: A {{ill|National Important Intangible Folk Cultural Asset|ja|重要無形民俗文化財|12=draft|12=draft}} from the {{ill|Hachinohe Region|ja|八戸市|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Aomori Prefecture|ja|青森県|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== References ==
* 『郷土史大辞典 下』（朝倉書店、2005th year ）ISBN 4-254-53013-7, p. 1066.
