'''Taue Odori''' (田植踊) is a form of {{ill|yoshuku performing arts|ja|予祝芸能|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Ta-asobi|lt=tanuki-themed ceremonies|ja|田遊び|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, primarily performed in the {{ill|Tohoku region|ja|東北地方|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} of Japan, particularly in {{ill|Miyagi Prefecture|ja|宮城県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Iwate Prefecture|ja|岩手県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, during the {{ill|Small New Year|ja|小正月|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} season. It is believed to have evolved into a {{ill|furyu dance|ja|風流踊|1=Furyu-odori|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}.
== Overview ==
Unlike {{ill|Ta-asobi|lt=tanuki-themed ceremonies|ja|田遊び|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, which often simulate {{ill|rice cultivation|ja|稲作|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} through symbolic gestures, Taue Odori is characterized by its strong {{ill|performance art|ja|芸能|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} aspects. It is typically performed by {{ill|village|ja|村|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|youth|ja|青年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|boys|ja|少年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|girls|ja|少女|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, accompanied by a leader called "Yajuro" and wearing {{ill|decorative flower hats|ja|花笠|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}. Performers visit {{ill|households|ja|住宅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, performing songs and dances, often following a recitation by Yajuro.
In some cases, the performance begins with a {{ill|dedication|ja|奉納|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} at {{ill|shrines|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} or {{ill|temples|ja|寺院|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} before visiting homes. Variations exist, such as the inclusion of {{ill|Ta-no-Kami|ja|田の神|Ta-no-Kami=Ta-no-Kami|lt=rice-field gods|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Seven Lucky Gods|ja|七福神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, celebrating the {{ill|New Year|ja|新年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} in unique ways.
== Representative Taue Odori Performances ==
* {{ill|Akiu no Taue Odori|ja|秋保の田植踊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}: A {{ill|UNESCO Intangible Cultural Heritage|ja|ユネスコ無形文化遺産|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} folk performing art from {{ill|Akihisa|ja|秋保町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Sendai City|ja|仙台市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Taihaku Ward|ja|太白区|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Miyagi Prefecture|ja|宮城県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Ayashi no Taue Odori|ja|愛子の田植踊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}: A folk performing art designated as a {{ill|Miyagi Prefecture Cultural Heritage|ja|宮城県指定文化財一覧#無形|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, from {{ill|Aiko|ja|愛子|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Aoba Ward|ja|青葉区|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, Sendai City. * {{ill|Tomiyama Taue Odori|ja|富谷田植踊り|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}: A folk performing art from {{ill|Tomiyama|ja|富谷市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, designated as an intangible cultural heritage of {{ill|Miyagi Prefecture|ja|宮城県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Yamaya Taue Odori|ja|山屋の田植踊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}: A {{ill|National Important Intangible Folk Cultural Asset|ja|重要無形民俗文化財|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} from {{ill|Yamaya|ja|紫波町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Shiwa District|ja|紫波郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Iwate Prefecture|ja|岩手県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Osawa Taue Odori|ja|大沢田植踊り|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}: A folk performing art designated as an intangible cultural heritage of {{ill|Takasaki City|ja|滝沢市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Iwate Prefecture|ja|岩手県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Kodashima Taue Odori|ja|小田島田植踊り|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}: A folk performing art from {{ill|Kodashima|ja|小田島|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, designated as an intangible cultural heritage of {{ill|Higashine City|ja|東根市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Yamagata Prefecture|ja|山形県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Ishii no Shichifukujin to Taue Odori|ja|石井の七福神と田植踊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}: A {{ill|National Important Intangible Folk Cultural Asset|ja|重要無形民俗文化財|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} from {{ill|Ishi District|ja|石東町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nishiki District|ja|錦町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Kita Toromi|ja|北トロミ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Nihonmatsu City|ja|二本松市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Tsubame Taue Odori|ja|津島の田植踊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}: A folk performing art designated as an intangible cultural heritage of {{ill|Namie Town|ja|浪江町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Futaba District|ja|双葉郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, Fukushima Prefecture. * {{ill|Inazawa Otaue Odori|ja|稲沢御田植踊り|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}: A folk performing art designated as an intangible cultural heritage of {{ill|Inazawa|ja|稲沢字梅ケ久保|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Motomiya City|ja|本宮市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}, Fukushima Prefecture. * {{ill|Hachinohe Enburi|ja|八戸のえんぶり|1=Enburi|2=ja|3=えんぶり|lt=Hachinohe Enburi|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}: A {{ill|National Important Intangible Folk Cultural Asset|ja|重要無形民俗文化財|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} from the {{ill|Hachinohe Region|ja|八戸市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Aomori Prefecture|ja|青森県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=draft}}.
